    "created_at": "2018-11-20T20:58:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-11-20T21:00:57Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think the first thing to establish here is exactly what use case this is trying to solve.\r\n\r\nWhen I look at this feature, I see this as a way to answer the question of \"I need more &lt;x&gt;, it is queued, but do I need to cancel other things so I can get it out faster?\". In this case, the ability to show information for all queued items IMO outweighs the fact that you need to hover to see it - you already know what you are interested in, and the information is only one action away.\r\n\r\nIts not clear to me (but i'm happy to be convinced otherwise) why it is necessary for the next item to be available passively."
  },
