    "updated_at": "2018-11-21T23:15:33Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Another use case is \"I have queued a,b,c but now I want to build c before b\". At the moment you have to cancel b for that. the \"Next\" indicator helps with this problem when you have a large queue and don't remember the order. An even bigger change but in line with the idea behind this would be to add an input for \"Next\" so that you don't have to remove items from the queue. However, I'm not sure if this problem justifies introducing more complexity. "
  },
